div.p:
I was most anxiously awaiting Mr Archer, having a parcel of plants ready for Sir Will Hooker, which I hoped he would take with him.
William Archer was leaving on an extended visit to England. Most thankful I shall be to Dr Milligan for his Endlich. genera;
Endlicher (1836-40); see M to R. Gunn, 20 May 1855. I will instantly send the amount for it and am so anxious to take the book on my next journey for which I am now preparing.
